<br>
You can't protect people from their own stupidity. You know what coffee is hot. If you spill it you might burn yourself.  You mother teaches you about scalding liquids as a kid for heaven sakes.<br>
<br>
If you buy a cup of coffee and choose to drink it while driving you are taking a risk.  Not only are you taking you rmind off the road you probaby arn't focused on the coffee either. <br>
<br>
A person with even AVERAGE intelligence shouldn't need a warning label on their coffee telling them its hot and could burn them! Sheesh.  We live in a society so wrapped up in law suits and blaming other folks for our own stupidity.  Take responsibility for yourself.<br>
<br>
As for buying items online for games.  I don't know.  I think its a bit cheap. But I agree that you shouldn't have to spend HOURS camping an item to get it.  Not all of us have that sort of time.  On the other hand do  I want to go into RvR against someone who spend hundreds on just hte right equipment. I don't know.  I guess its their choice if that's how they choose to spend their money.   <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn - Warden of Connla<BR>
